general.description:
I am a Senior Associate in Minter Ellison's Human Resources & Industrial Relations practice in Perth, Western Australia.

I have clients in a range of industries including mining, utilities, rail, health care, storage and handling, media and local government. I provide clients with tailored, commercial legal advice across all aspects of workplace relations and safety.

My experience includes:
- representing clients in the various workplace tribunals on a range of matters including industrial disputes; unfair dismissals, general protections claims and equal opportunity complaints;
- advising on industrial issues such as industrial strategy, union right of entry, industrial action and collective bargaining;
- advising local governments on industrial issues arising from amalgamation and boundary change;
- advising on the management of bullying complaints and workplace investigations;
- advising listed companies on termination benefit restrictions
- providing strategic advice on corporate restructures and transmission of business matters;
- advising on all aspects of employee management including disciplinary and performance management processes and outcomes;
- advising on the management of ill/injured workers, absenteeism and the return to work process
- involvement in the development and variation of several Federal modern awards; and
- advising on occupational health and safety obligations including key topics such as incident response and drug and alcohol testing.

Specialties: Human Resources, Industrial Relations

